commits.commitMessage:
Implement new vPortSuppressTicksAndSleep for stateful standby.

The old vPortSuppressTicksAndSleep would use a constant tick adjustment
to handle time spent with SysTick disabled.  As hibernate_to_gpm() and
hibernate_from_gpm() take several 100 ms to complete, and the time required
depends on the data being compressed, this was insufficient.  Create
a new implementation which uses SysTick to track time spent compressing and
decompressing, and adjust the time to sleep based on this.

The new function will also gracefully degrade from stateful standby to stop
mode if all retained data cannot be compressed to GPM.

Resolves: LE-15903
Change-Id: I09ba1f354c2bc9406117a3ae62d5c8a61b1f64d8
commits.subject: Implement new vPortSuppressTicksAndSleep for stateful standby.

commits.commitMessage:
Adjust linker script for stateful hibernation

Modify the linker script to support stateful hibernation by:

   1) Combining both GPM regions into one.  Separate GPM regions are not
      needed -- stateful hibernation will automatically preserve only the
      GPM memory which is required.
   2) Set up uncompressed and compressed regions of GPM.  Uncompressed
      memory contains the stacks & vairables needed to perform
      compression and decompression, and one block of free space to jump
      start the compression process.
   3) Explicitly define which memory regions contain what variables.
      Automatic splitting no longer works with the new, more complex
      linker map.

Resolves: LE-15901
Change-Id: I3fca10009371fa5733992107b8b91847d09b4382
commits.subject: Adjust linker script for stateful hibernation

commits.commitMessage:
Implement stateful hibernation for ALT1250 MCU

This change adds a new option configSWI_STATEFUL_STANDBY which will
use a stateful hibernate for the ALT1250 MCU.  With this option
enabled, triggering standby mode will cause the MCU to resume operation
where it left off after exiting standby mode.

This is accomplished as follows:

    1) When entering hibernation, the state of the NVIC is saved
       to GPM.
    2) The standby code calls standby_enter_lower(), which saves
       the contents of all callee-preserved registers to the stack,
       and saves the stack pointer to the current TCB.
    3) The PMP is then notified the MCU is ready to enter standby,
       at which point the MCU core is powered off.
    4) When the MCU is woken up, it will check if the contents of
       GPM memory are still present.  If so, it resotres the
       callee-reserved registers from the stack, then restores
       the LR to the PC.  This makes it appear the MCU has
       returned from standby_enter_lower() (above).
    5) The state of the NVIC is restored, and execution resumes.

NOTE: This has been tested with PwrManager demo app.  Currently the
UART does not function correctly after resuming from standby.
This behaviour is not observed on the eval board.  For this reason
the code is DISABLED as it does not work correctly.

Resolves: LE-16131
Change-Id: I3ee1a87bd60e15e394fad6e953d5042f8e85d064
commits.subject: Implement stateful hibernation for ALT1250 MCU
